<title>Volume of Dodecahedron</title>

<h1>Volume of Dodecahedron</h1>
<br>
<i>The platonic dodecahedron has 12 sides, 20 vertices and 30 edges</i>
<center><img src=3D"http://cubeman.org/dod7.gif">
</center>
<br>
<br>Formula for Volume =3D ((15 + 7 * sqrt(5)) /4 ) * s^3
<br>where s =3D side length
<br>e.g. A dodecahedron of edge length 1 cm would have a volume of 7.663 cu=
bic centimeters
